Permanent-stall observability hole + fix (2026-06-01): plugkit turn.end fires ONLY in turnTick when a NEW verb arrives after >TURN_IDLE_MS - a turn that never receives another verb stays open forever and emits ZERO event, so a permanent mid-chain stall is SILENCE not signal and gmsniff cannot flag what was never emitted. FIX: scanStalledTurns() in plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js wired to a 30s heartbeat interval emits deviation.mid-chain-stall once per stall episode (one-shot via t.stallEmitted, reset on resuming verb) for open turns idle>300s whose lastPhase is non-terminal OR prdPending>0; skips authorized COMPLETE-idle. turnTick extended to capture prdPending from data.prd_pending_count. gmsniff needs NO change - it surfaces any deviation.* prefix generically. NOTE deploy: wrapper edits live in repo but the running watcher loads ~/.gm-tools/ installed copy; ships only after gm-plugkit republishes via cascade.